Changes:

- updated `playlist:update` script
   If there is an unclosed pull request during the update process, there is a high probability of a [merge conflict](https://docs.github.com/en/pull-requests/collaborating-with-pull-requests/addressing-merge-conflicts/about-merge-conflicts). To avoid this, the most destructive operations (URLs normalization and link sorting) have been moved to a separate script.
- created `playlist:format` script
   This script will [normalize URLs](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/URI_normalization), remove duplicate links, erase invalid `tvg-id` and sort links by channel name, quality and label.
- created `format` workflow
   This workflow sequentially runs the `api:load`, `playlist:format`, `playlist:lint` and `playlist:validate` scripts. 
   At first, the workflow will be run manually to make sure it does not affect pull requests..
- deleted `db:create` script
   The script is no longer needed as links are now loaded directly from internal playlists.
- updated [Contributing Guide](https://github.com/iptv-org/iptv/blob/0739182d6d49d83e7cd73e85f053aff3bc2eae3d/CONTRIBUTING.md#scripts)

Changes:

- Added automatic processing of requests from [Issues](https://github.com/iptv-org/iptv/issues) tab.
   For a request to be processed by the bot, it must have one of these labels: `streams:add`, `streams:edit`, `streams:remove`, as well as the `approved` label.
- Updated GitHub Actions [workflows](https://github.com/iptv-org/iptv/tree/master/.github/workflows).
   Playlists will now be updated once a day at 0:00 UTC to reduce the chance of conflicts in manually created pull requests.
   During the update the [iptv-bot](https://github.com/apps/iptv-bot) should process all approved requests received during the day, [normalize](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/URI_normalization) URLs, sort links by channel name, quality, label and url, generate updated public playlists, update [streams.json](https://github.com/iptv-org/api?tab=readme-ov-file#streams) file and update playlist list in [README.md](https://github.com/iptv-org/iptv/blob/master/README.md#playlists).
- All scripts in the repository are rewritten using [TypeScript](https://www.typescriptlang.org/).
  This should make the code a bit easier to read if someone decides to work on it in the future.
- Updated [Issue Templates](https://docs.github.com/en/communities/using-templates-to-encourage-useful-issues-and-pull-requests/about-issue-and-pull-request-templates#issue-templates).
   - Added a form for requests to remove links from a playlist.
   - When adding a new link or editing the description of an existing one, you can now also specify the custom channel name, user-agent, http referrer and maximum broadcast quality.
- Updated [Contributing Guide](https://github.com/iptv-org/iptv/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md).
    - "Issue Report Guidelines" and "Pull Request Guidelines" have been merged into the "How to?" section.
    - Added a link to the [blocklist](https://github.com/iptv-org/database/blob/master/data/blocklist.csv) (https://github.com/iptv-org/iptv/issues/14184#issuecomment-1714039730). 
    - Added description of sorting order of links in playlists (https://github.com/orgs/iptv-org/discussions/1452).
    - Added a section with a short description of all [scripts](https://github.com/iptv-org/iptv/blob/090760e73a02fb74e6efdca58f47f14a814a62b3/package.json#L3-L23).
    - Added a section with a short description of all [workflows](https://github.com/iptv-org/iptv/tree/master/.github/workflows).

This update adds two GitHub workflows:

- `check`: will check each pull request for syntax errors
- `update`: will update public playlists every 6 hours

Both workspaces can be tested locally using the [Docker](https://www.docker.com/) and [nektos/act](https://github.com/nektos/act) utility. After installing it, you need to start Docker and run the following commands:

```sh
npm run act:check
```

and

```sh
npm run act:update
```

Adds a new NPM script that allows you to quickly get a list of all channel requests and their current status.

```sh
┌─────────┬─────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────┬──────────────┐
│ (index) │ issueNumber │              channelId               │    status    │
├─────────┼─────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────┼──────────────┤
│    0    │    5781     │            'TVCiudad.uy'             │  'pending'   │
│    1    │    5782     │             'Canal5.uy'              │  'pending'   │
│    2    │    5956     │               'RDS.ca'               │  'pending'   │
...
```

A list of possible statuses:

- `pending`: not yet resolved
- `fullfilled`: channel is already in the playlist
- `duplicate`: there is already a similar request
- `invalid_id`: the channel with the specified ID is not in the [iptv-org/database](https://github.com/iptv-org/database)
- `error`: there is an error in the request that prevents it from being processed

The command to run the script: 

```sh
npm run api:load && npm run report:create
```

or just

```sh
npm run report
```

The correct channel ID is `Vitebsk.by`, the link to which is already on the playlist:
